snippet.textDisplay: i feel like grays anatomy has been dragged out to nothingness. After the end of season 10, once Sandra Oh's character leaves, 3/5 of the original interns are left at the hospital, and soon after many other important characters are written off. Now in the 16? season, the plot lines are uninteresting and there is nothing new or sentimental bringing anybody in. The only viewers of the show now are diehard fans who watching for the very few people remaining who actually have developed storylines. Overall, I feel like it should have ended in season 10. They had the perfect set up to let cristina leave, meredith move to DC with derek and map the brain, and alex and jo could have stayed at Grey-Sloan and run the place, wrapping up the story nicely in a bow.

snippet.textDisplay:
Okay but what about the shows that were AMAZING but got randomly cancelled and left at a cliffhanger ?

There was this AMAZING show that had Will Forte and Kristen Schaal in it (produced by Forte, as well), called "Last Man on Earth". I loved that show, but NOBODY knew about it (which is, I'm assuming, the reason it probably got cancelled). Other than my household, I knew only 1 other person that watched it; however, they also loved it as much as we did.
I was so sad to see such a big cliffhanger, with knowing that there would be no proper conclusion. I was so so so sad, as it had become one of my favorite shows ... or actually, one of the few shows I would look forward to watching on cable (satellite? is that what it is now?)

snippet.textDisplay:
The Good Place just ended, and I think the finale was perfect. I don't know if they'll stretch it out in the form of spin-offs or something, but at least the main show is over.



SPOILERS INCOMING


If they wanted to, I think they could have squeezed out another season, maybe about the characters' time in the Good Place. They could have left it at the penultimate episode, leaving room for more. But I really appreciate the fact that we, the audience, actually had to say goodbye to these characters and confront the fact that they're gone. It was a natural ending, in my opinion.

snippet.textDisplay:
So, Supernatural was originally slated to end with the Season 5 finale. I personally enjoyed the way it ended and think it's a very fitting conclusion to the story. But now the show is on... Season 14.

It's very obviously being milked and I have friends who still watch the show as if it isn't the same 4 plotlines being repeated over and over again. But they're too attached to the characters to stop.

Every time I suggest SPN to someone I tell them to stop after Season 5 because it was supposed to end there. The other seasons are fun, yes. But they're also ridiculous and far beyond a 'supernatural' themed show.
